A vintage-style illustration of an intricate mechanical puzzle box being carefully disassembled and reassembled, with layers of nested compartments visible in cross-section. The box sits on a worn wooden workbench scattered with antique tools, magnifying glasses, and curled parchment scrolls. Golden light streams through a dusty workshop window, illuminating floating particles and casting warm shadows. The puzzle box features ornate brass fittings and complex interlocking mechanisms, some pieces slightly misaligned, suggesting a delicate restoration process. Muted sepia tones with touches of copper and deep burgundy dominate the color palette, evoking the feeling of patient, meticulous technical work on something with a long and complicated history.
